The paper discusses techniques for improving the generalization of deep neural networks on classification tasks, which is a common topic in machine learning research. The use of regularization techniques such as $\ell_2$ regularization, dropout, and batch normalization suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The mention of entropy-driven SGD suggests a possible connection to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. The use of deep architectures trained on CIFAR-10 and MNIST suggests a possible connection to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The focus on classification tasks suggests a possible connection to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the mention of data augmentation techniques suggests a possible connection to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category, which includes natural language processing and other tasks involving text and speech data.
